---
import "../styles/global.css";
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Our Technology - Cambridge Construction Intelligence</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>

  <body>
    <Header />

    <!-- Section 1: Technology Overview Grid -->
    <section class="technology-overview">
      <div class="container tech-grid">
        <!-- Left column: Heading -->
        <h2>Our Technology</h2>

        <!-- Right column: Paragraphs -->
        <div>
          <p>
            Our technology is the result of over five years of cutting-edge research and development 
            at the University of Cambridge, created in close partnership with leading construction 
            companies across the UK. This unique combination of academic rigor and real-world testing 
            has produced a platform that brings unprecedented clarity, consistency, and intelligence 
            to construction performance.
          </p>
          <p>
            We combine advanced data integration, automated analytics, and domain-specialised metrics 
            to transform fragmented project data into reliable, near real-time productivity insight.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 2: Integrates Siloed Data Automatically Grid -->
    <section class="data-integration">
      <div class="container tech-grid">
        <!-- Left column: Heading and subheading -->
        <div>
        <h2>What It Does</h2>
        <p class="subtitle">Integrates Siloed Data Automatically</p>

        </div>

        <!-- Right column: Content list -->
        <div>
                    <p>
            Construction projects generate enormous volumes of digital and manual data; but most of 
            it is fragmented across systems, formats, and subcontractors.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our AI platform automatically ingests and integrates data from multiple sources, including:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Programme and planning data</li>
            <li>Progress and field reporting systems</li>
            <li>Imaging and visual data</li>
            <li>Digital tools (BIM, sensors, logistics platforms, and more)</li>
            <li>Contractor-specific datasets and spreadsheets</li>
          </ul>
          <p>This creates a single, coherent, structured view of performance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 3: Integrated Intelligence with Background Image -->
    <section class="integrated-intelligence">
    <div class="hero-bg">
        <div class="overlay"></div> <!-- subtle overlay -->
        <div class="content-box">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <p class="subtitle">Integrated Intelligence for Real-Time Productivity Insight</p>
        <p>
            Our AI platform transforms fragmented construction data into structured, standardised 
            intelligence that teams can act on. Using advanced data processing, AI-assisted cleaning 
            and domain-specific modelling, we generate reliable productivity metrics such as 
            activity-level production rates, flowline analysis, plan-vs-actual performance, and the 
            identification of blockers and workflow constraints.
        </p>
        <p>
            By continuously unifying diverse data streams, the system provides near real-time situational 
            awareness; highlighting emerging delays, productivity losses, rework, and risks before 
            they escalate. This visibility enables teams to intervene early, optimise workflows, and 
            make faster, evidence-based decisions.
        </p>
        <p>
            Because all projects are measured consistently, the platform also produces robust, 
            evidence-based benchmarks that improve future planning. These insights strengthen 
            tendering and pricing decisions, challenge unrealistic programmes, support MMC and 
            modern delivery methods, and drive continuous learning across projects and organisations.
        </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    </section>


    <!-- Section 4: Underlying Technology (4-column layout) -->
    <section class="underlying-technology">
    <div class="container tech-grid-4col">

        <!-- Column 1: Section heading -->
        <div>
        <h2>Our Underlying Technology</h2>
        </div>

        <!-- Column 2: Two subheadings -->
        <div>
        <h3 class="subtitle">Custom Data Integration Framework</h3>
        <p>A flexible ingestion pipeline designed for constructionâ€™s messy, inconsistent data. Handles structured, semi-structured, and unstructured formats.</p>

        <h3 class="subtitle">AI-Assisted Data Cleaning & Standardisation</h3>
        <p>Machine learning methods trained on real project data plus domain rules developed through Cambridge research.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Column 3: One subheading -->
        <div>
        <h3 class="subtitle">Construction-Specific Analytics Engine</h3>
        <p>Purpose-built algorithms for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Flowline modelling</li>
            <li>Production forecasting</li>
            <li>Constraint and blocker detection</li>
            <li>Workspace and workflow analysis</li>
            <li>Multi-project benchmarking</li>
        </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Column 4: Two subheadings -->
        <div>
        <h3 class="subtitle">Novel Visualisation Methods</h3>
        <p>Developed through research and validated in industry pilots, our visualisations make ground truth immediately understandable and reveal insights traditional dashboards cannot show.</p>

        <h3 class="subtitle">Scalable Cloud Architecture</h3>
        <p>Designed for multi-project deployment, security, and integration with existing digital ecosystems.</p>
        </div>

    </div>
    </section>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>

body {
  font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
}

/* Add spacing at the top of the page */
.technology-overview {
  padding-top: 75px; /* adjust the value as needed */
}

/* Technology and Data-Integration grids */
.tech-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.8fr; /* left smaller, right wider */
  gap: 40px;
  align-items: start;
  margin-bottom: 60px;
}

.tech-grid h2 {
  font-size: 36px;
  color: #333F48;
  margin: 0;
}

.tech-grid p {
  font-size: 18px;
  color: #333F48;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.tech-grid ul {
  margin-top: 12px;
  padding-left: 20px;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .tech-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 24px;
  }

  .tech-grid h2 {
    font-size: 28px;
  }

  .tech-grid p {
    font-size: 16px;
  }
}

.integrated-intelligence {
  position: relative;
  width: 100%;
  background: url('/hero3.png') center/cover no-repeat; /* updated image */
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: 100px 0;
}

.integrated-intelligence .hero-bg {
  position: relative;
  width: 100%;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
}



.integrated-intelligence .content-box {
  position: relative;
  background: #fff; /* fully opaque */
  padding: 40px;
  max-width: 60%;
  border-radius: 12px;
  box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
  z-index: 2; /* above overlay */
}

.integrated-intelligence .content-box h2 {
  font-size: 32px;
  margin-bottom: 24px;
  color: #333F48;
}

.integrated-intelligence .content-box p {
  font-size: 18px;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: #333F48;
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}

/* Responsive */
@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .integrated-intelligence .content-box {
    max-width: 80%;
    padding: 30px;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .integrated-intelligence .content-box {
    max-width: 95%;
    padding: 24px;
  }

  .integrated-intelligence .content-box h2 {
    font-size: 28px;
  }

  .integrated-intelligence .content-box p {
    font-size: 16px;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .integrated-intelligence {
    padding: 60px 0;
  }
}

/* 4-column grid for Underlying Technology */
.underlying-technology {
  margin-top: 75px; /* space from previous section */
}

/* 4-column grid for Underlying Technology */
.tech-grid-4col {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr 1fr; /* 4 equal columns */
  gap: 40px;
  align-items: start;
  margin-bottom: 60px;
}

.tech-grid-4col h2 {
  font-size: 36px;
  color: #333F48;
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.tech-grid-4col h3.subtitle {
  color: #E9560D;  /* subtitle color */
  font-weight: bold; 
  font-size: 18px;
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.tech-grid-4col p {
  font-size: 16px;
  color: #333F48;
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.tech-grid-4col ul {
  padding-left: 20px;
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}

/* Responsive: stack columns on smaller screens */
@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .tech-grid-4col {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; /* 2 columns */
    gap: 24px;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .tech-grid-4col {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr; /* stack all columns */
    gap: 24px;
  }

  .tech-grid-4col h2 {
    font-size: 28px;
  }

  .tech-grid-4col h3.subtitle {
    font-size: 16px;
  }

  .tech-grid-4col p {
    font-size: 14px;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  body,
  .tech-grid,
  .tech-grid h2,
  .tech-grid p,
  .tech-grid-4col,
  .tech-grid-4col h2,
  .tech-grid-4col h3.subtitle,
  .tech-grid-4col p {
    font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
  }
}

</style>